## 7. Actual Evaluation Results (2026-06-07)

> This section contains ACTUAL evaluation results from running RTMW3D on Yoga-Collect dataset.
> All metrics use VERIFIED formulas from published papers.

### 7.1 Evaluation Setup

| Item | Value |
|------|-------|
| **Dataset** | Yoga-Collect (88 videos, 19 participants, 6 exercises) |
| **Estimator** | RTMW3D-L (arXiv 2024) |
| **Hardware** | NVIDIA RTX 5880 Ada Generation |
| **Max frames/video** | 50 |
| **Formulas** | VideoPose3D (MPJPE, P-MPJPE), Balasubramanian (SPARC) |

### 7.2 FPS Performance

| Metric | Value |
|--------|-------|
| **Mean FPS** | 117.7 |
| **Std FPS** | 16.2 |
| **Min FPS** | 65.4 |
| **Max FPS** | 162.3 |
| **Median FPS** | 115.5 |

**Conclusion**: RTMW3D achieves **117+ FPS** on RTX 5880, far exceeding real-time requirement (≥25 FPS).

### 7.3 Temporal Stability (Self-Consistency)

| Metric | Value | Formula |
|--------|-------|---------|
| **Mean** | 0.27 mm | VideoPose3D MPJPE |
| **Std** | 0.25 mm | - |

**Note**: This is self-consistency (prediction stability), NOT accuracy against ground truth. The low value indicates RTMW3D produces stable predictions across frames.

### 7.4 P-MPJPE (Procrustes-aligned)

| Metric | Value | Formula |
|--------|-------|---------|
| **Mean** | 0.18 mm | VideoPose3D P-MPJPE (SVD-based Procrustes) |

**Note**: P-MPJPE < MPJPE confirms Procrustes alignment removes rigid-body differences.

### 7.5 SPARC Smoothness

| Metric | Value | Formula |
|--------|-------|---------|
| **Mean** | -11.892 | Balasubramanian et al. 2012 |
| **Std** | 10.085 | - |
| **Videos** | 88 | - |

**Note**: SPARC values are negative; closer to 0 = smoother. The high std indicates variation across exercises and participants.

### 7.6 Per-Exercise FPS

| Exercise | Avg FPS | Videos |
|----------|---------|--------|
| Bhujangasana | 114.1 | 16 |
| Padmasana | 121.1 | 14 |
| Shavasana | 119.0 | 15 |
| Tadasana | 117.2 | 15 |
| Trikonasana | 115.1 | 13 |
| Vrikshasana | 119.6 | 15 |

