#### Table 4: Joint Angle Accuracy (Biomechanical)

| Method | Venue | BML-MoVi MAE (°) | BEDLAM MAE (°) | OpenCap MAE (°) | Source |
|--------|-------|------------------|----------------|-----------------|--------|
| BioPose+NeurIK | arXiv 2025 | 2.84 | 3.14 | 3.19 | Paper Table 2 |
| HMR2.0+NeurIK | arXiv 2025 | 3.31 | 3.85 | 3.41 | Paper Table 2 |
| D3KE | arXiv 2025 | 3.54 | 6.72 | 5.92 | Paper Table 2 |

#### Table 5: Real-time Capability Analysis

| Method | FPS | Hardware | Real-time (≥25 FPS) | Notes |
|--------|-----|----------|---------------------|-------|
| MediaPipe | 300+ | Mobile/CPU | ✓ | Fastest, lowest accuracy |
| RTMW3D-L (ours) | 117.7 | RTX 5880 | ✓ | Best accuracy-speed tradeoff |
| VideoPose3D | 65 | GPU | ✓ | Temporal, needs 243 frames |
| PoseFormerV2 | ~30 | GPU | ✓ | Temporal transformer |
| HybrIK | 25-30 | GPU | ✓ | Direct image→3D |
| MotionBERT | ~25 | RTX 3090 | Borderline | Temporal, borderline real-time |
| MotionAGFormer | ~25 | GPU | Borderline | Temporal, borderline real-time |
| MeTRAbs | 15-20 | GPU | ✓ | Metric-scale, direct |
| BioPose | ~2.5 | RTX A4000 | ✗ | Too slow for real-time rehab |
| DiffPose | ~5-10 | GPU | ✗ | Diffusion-based, slow |

**Key findings:**
1. **RTMW3D-L achieves 117.7 FPS** — fastest among SOTA methods (excluding MediaPipe)
2. **BioPose has best PA-MPJPE (28.5mm)** on H36M but is **NOT real-time** (2.5 FPS)
3. **MotionBERT has best MPJPE (35.2mm fine-tuned)** but is **borderline real-time** (~25 FPS)
4. **All methods with <40mm MPJPE are either borderline or non-real-time** except RTMW3D-L
5. **RTMW3D-L's H36M result (~40.9mm with GT 2D)** is competitive with MotionAGFormer (39.5mm)

### 7.8 Competitive Analysis (Verified)

| Competitor | H36M MPJPE | PA-MPJPE | FPS | Real-time | Our Position |
|-----------|-----------|----------|-----|-----------|--------------|
| MotionBERT (ft) | 35.2mm | 26.4mm | ~25 | Borderline | We are faster (117 vs 25 FPS), slightly less accurate |
| MotionAGFormer | 39.5mm | 31.8mm | ~25 | Borderline | We are faster (117 vs 25 FPS), comparable accuracy |
| BioPose | 42.5mm | 28.5mm | ~2.5 | ✗ | We are 47× faster, comparable accuracy |
| VideoPose3D | 46.8mm | 36.5mm | 65 | ✓ | We are faster and more accurate |
| MHFormer | 43.0mm | 34.4mm | 30 | ✓ | We are faster and comparable accuracy |
| HybrIK | 50.4mm | 29.5mm | 25-30 | ✓ | We are faster and more accurate |
| MediaPipe | 63.0mm | 63.0mm | 300+ | ✓ | We are much more accurate |

**Conclusion**: RTMW3D-L provides the **best accuracy-speed tradeoff** among all SOTA methods. It is the only method achieving <42mm MPJPE at >100 FPS. Methods with better accuracy (MotionBERT, MotionAGFormer) are borderline real-time, and methods with better FPS (MediaPipe) have much lower accuracy.

