## 8. Related Work: Papers with Similar Contributions

> This section lists papers that share contributions with ADAPT-Rehab.
> Use these for comparison tables and to position our work in the literature.

---

### 8.1 CV-Based Rehabilitation Systems

#### Paper 1: Pose Trainer (2020)
- **Citation**: Ren, R., Chen, C., & Xu, C. (2020). "Pose Trainer: Correcting Exercise Posture using Pose Estimation." *arXiv:2006.11718*.
- **GitHub**: -
- **Overlap**: Contribution 1 (CV-based rehab system)
- **Methods**: OpenPose (2D) + vector geometry + rule-based feedback
- **Results**: ~85-90% accuracy on form correctness classification
- **Limitations**: 2D only, no 3D, no voice/LLM, no pain detection, no smoothness metrics
- **Compare on**: Feedback quality, number of exercises, pose dimensionality

#### Paper 2: Vakanski et al. (2018)
- **Citation**: Vakanski, A. et al. (2018). "A data set of human body movements for physical rehabilitation exercises." *Data*, 3(1), 2.
- **GitHub**: https://webpages.uidaho.edu/ui-prmd/
- **Overlap**: Contribution 1 (automated rehab assessment)
- **Methods**: HMMs with pose-based features for exercise scoring
- **Results**: Scoring correlation with clinical assessments
- **Limitations**: No real-time feedback, no 3D pose, no multimodal
- **Compare on**: Scoring accuracy on UI-PRMD dataset

#### Paper 3: Marusic et al. (2025)
- **Citation**: Marusic, A., Nguyen, S.M., & Tapus, A. (2025). "Skeleton-Based Transformer for Classification of Errors and Better Feedback in Low Back Pain Physical Rehabilitation Exercises." *ICORR 2025*.
- **GitHub**: -
- **Overlap**: Contribution 1 (rehab exercise assessment)
- **Methods**: Transformer on skeleton sequences; joint importance calculation
- **Results**: Surpasses SOTA on KERAAL dataset for error classification
- **Limitations**: Error classification only, no scoring, no feedback system
- **Compare on**: Classification accuracy, feedback granularity

---

### 8.2 3D Pose Estimation for Rehabilitation

#### Paper 4: RePose (2025)
- **Citation**: Xue, Y., Smirnov, S., Li, Z. et al. (2025). "RePose: Real-Time 3D Human Pose Estimation and Biomechanical Analysis Framework for Rehabilitation." *arXiv preprint*.
- **GitHub**: -
- **Overlap**: Contribution 2 (3D pose for rehab) — **DIRECT COMPETITOR**
- **Methods**: Real-time 3D pose estimation + biomechanical analysis
- **Results**: Framework for rehabilitation with 3D pose
- **Limitations**: No LLM coaching, no pain detection, no elderly-specific design
- **Compare on**: MPJPE, joint angle MAE, real-time FPS

#### Paper 5: RTMPose / RTMW3D (2023)
- **Citation**: Jiang, T. et al. (2023). "RTMPose: Real-Time Multi-Person Pose Estimation based on MMPose." *arXiv:2303.07399*.
- **GitHub**: https://github.com/open-mmlab/mmpose
- **Overlap**: Contribution 2 (our pose backbone)
- **Methods**: Top-down pose estimation with CSPNeXt backbone
- **Results**: SOTA on COCO/MPII benchmarks, 98+ FPS
- **Limitations**: Not rehab-specific, no feedback system
- **Compare on**: Speed vs accuracy tradeoff

#### Paper 6: MeTRAbs (2021)
- **Citation**: Sarandi, I. et al. (2021). "MeTRAbs: Metric-Scale Truncation-Robust Heatmaps for Absolute 3D Human Pose Estimation." *WACV 2021*.
- **GitHub**: https://github.com/isarandi/metrabs
- **Overlap**: Contribution 2 (metric-scale 3D pose)
- **Methods**: Direct image-to-3D with metric-scale output (centimeters)
- **Results**: SOTA on MuPoTS-3D, H36M, 3DPW
- **Limitations**: Standalone estimator, no rehab system, no feedback
- **Compare on**: MPJPE, metric-scale accuracy

---

